9. Duties After Loss. The Insured must:
(a) give prompt notice to Us of the loss;
(b) notify the police in case of loss by theft;
(c) protect the property from further damage and keep an accurate record
of repair expenses;
(d) cooperate with Us in the investigation and settlement of the claim;
(e) prepare an inventory of damaged personal property showing the
quantity, description, actual cash value, and amount of loss;
(f) submit to examination under oath, if requested;
(g) produce for examination all pertinent records and documents in the
Insured’s possession.

10. Loss Settlement. We will settle losses to:
(a) Coverage A and B on the basis of replacement cost without deduction
for depreciation, subject to the following:
(i) The Insured must repair or replace the damaged property within two
years after the date of loss;
(ii) The amount we will pay for loss to such property is the lesser of:
(A) the limit of liability shown in the Declarations for such property;
(B) the replacement cost of such property; or
(C) the amount actually spent to repair or replace such property.
(b) Coverage C on the basis of actual cash value at the time of loss.

15. Exclusions Applicable to Coverage E and F. Coverage E and F do not
apply to:
(a) bodily injury or property damage which is expected or intended by the
Insured;
(b) bodily injury or property damage arising out of business pursuits of
an Insured or the rental of any premises;
(c) bodily injury or property damage arising out of the ownership,
maintenance, use, loading, unloading, entrustment to others, or existence
of any aircraft, motor vehicle, or watercraft owned or operated by or
rented or loaned to an Insured;
(d) bodily injury or property damage arising out of the transmission of a
communicable disease by an Insured;
(e) bodily injury or property damage arising out of sexual molestation,
corporal punishment, or physical or mental abuse;
(f) bodily injury or property damage arising out of the use, sale,
manufacture, delivery, transfer, or possession of a controlled substance.
